<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-189-206 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 645 658</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  April 1991 v11 n4 p61(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Integrated fax server for NetWare from Xerox. (Xerox LAN/FaxExpress 21 system unveiled) (New Products) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Xerox Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    XRX.andO;Product:   Xerox LAN/Fax Express 21 (Facsimile transceiver) (Productintroduction)NetWare (Network operating system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFacsimileIntegrated Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>An integrated fax server that allows Novell NetWare users to send and receivefacsimile transmissions directly at personal computers or workstations wasannounced by Xerox Corporation at the recent NetWorld show.andM;The Xerox LAN/Fax Express 21 system consists of a Xerox Telecopier 7021plain-paper facsimile terminal and the LAN/Fax Express hardware accessory andsoftware.andM;With the LAN/Fax Express 21, users can fax computer-generated documents froma pop-up window without leaving the computer application, such as a wordprocessing or spreadsheet program.andP;  The software includes more than 350 fontsand supports the Hewlett-Packard LaserJet PCL page description language, aswell as ASCII and PCX.andM;When sending a fax, users type the destination telephone number or select thenumber or distribution list from an on-line directory.andP;  On any faxtransmission, users can select several operating parameters, includingresolution, the inclusion of a cover page, and immediate or delayedtransmission.andM;Incoming faxes can be printed on the 7021 facsimile terminal or an optionaldedicated laser printer, or stored electronically in the network file server.andO;Incoming faxes also can be directed automatically to confidential mailboxesusing pre-selected touch-tone codes.andP;  Network users can access a list offaxes in their mailboxes and then view, print, save, route, re-fax, or deleteeach fax.andM;LAN/Fax Express 21 also allows users to scan documents into the network forstorage in a PCX graphics format.andP;  Once a document has been scanned, it canbe viewed, routed to others on the LAN, stored, printed, or re-faxed.andP;  TheXerox LAN/Fax Express 21 system carries a single-unit list price of $6,995,which includes a Xerox Telecopier 7021 facsimile terminal, RS-232-Cinterface, and LAN/Fax Express 21 accessory.andP;  Customers who own a Xerox 7020or 7021 fax can upgrade their machines and purchase the LAN/Fax Express 21accessory at the single-unit list price of $2,995.andM;Order-taking for the LAN/Fax Express 21 began March 1 in Washington, DC,Chicago, Los Angeles, and Atlanta, through Xerox Facsimile Account Managers;national order-taking is expected to begin July 1.andM;Information:  Larry Jones, Xerox Corporation, Xerox Square, Rochester, NY14644; 800) 832-6979, ext. 521B.andO;</TEXT></DOC>